title: Facebook may have vastly overpaid in data privacy settlement: court filing
text: Facebook Inc may have paid $4.9 billion more than the maximum penalty it faced under a settlement agreement with regulators related to allegations it mishandled user privacy, according to a Wednesday court ruling.

title: Facebook is reportedly working on a competitor to the buzzy new social media app Clubhouse (FB)
text: Facebook has a team working on a new project that aims to replicate the core functionality of the buzzy new social media app, Clubhouse, the New York Times reported on Wednesday. The Facebook project is intended to create audio-based chat rooms for users, the report said, but it's still in the early stages.

title: Facebook Is Said to Be Building a Product to Compete With Clubhouse
text: The social network, which has a history of cloning its competitors, has started working on an audio chat product.

title: EU privacy agency urges more safeguards to curb U.S. tech giants
text: EU privacy watchdog EDPS on Wednesday backed the bloc's push to curb the power of Apple, Amazon, Alphabet unit Google and Facebook via new tough rules and suggested more safeguards to boost users' privacy rights.

title: Facebook will temporarily show less political content to some users
text: Facebook will temporarily reduce the amount of political content on News Feed for a small percentage of users in certain countries.

title: Facebook Short Interest on the Rise Again
text: For years, Facebook Inc. (NASDAQ: FB) faced questions about how much it does or does not respect the privacy of its users.

title: Facebook removes hundreds of fake accounts tied to Uganda, Palestine
text: The social network says a group of fake accounts had links to a government agency in Uganda.
